&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Contract Support Officer - Band 5&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Permanent &lt;br /&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Full Time - 37.5 hours per week&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen within NHS North East Essex Clinical Commissioning Group’s busy Contracts team for a Contract Support Officer. &lt;br /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The post holder will be responsible for supporting the team with management of their portfolio of healthcare contracts and assisting with development and maintenance of project plans and databases. &lt;br /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The role will require excellent administration skills (including minute taking to a high standard), an attention to detail that is reflected in verbal and written communication, as well as excellent interpersonal skills to deal with complex and sensitive matters that may arise in day-to-day business. The post holder will be expected to have a credible presence with stakeholders including providers and GP elected members. The right candidate will also need the ability to work under pressure and manage competing priorities.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The post holder will be expected to work with colleagues including Business Intelligence, Finance, Quality and Commissioning and other CCGs, to assist in the management of all elements of the contracts within the CCG portfolio. The post holder will need to be able to demonstrate excellent organisational skills and an attention to detail that is reflected in verbal and written communication. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The role will be a challenging but rewarding opportunity for the right candidate. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Should you wish to discuss the role further, please contact Carolyn Kadlec via &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;ckadlec@nhs.net &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
